skills to inspect and maintain wood-burning freestanding stoves in compliance with NCSG standards. This course features interactive slide content, desktop-based activities, realistic simulations, and detailed testing. Users are challenged to perform inspections with randomized issues in a virtual residential setting, ensuring all necessary procedures are followed.\n\n**VR Controls and PPE \u2013** Learn how to navigate the virtual environment while getting acquainted with essential personal protective equipment.\n\n**Responsibility & Worksite Hazard Assessment \u2013** Operate in a simulated environment to identify and mitigate hazards commonly encountered during inspections of wood-burning freestanding stoves.\n\n**Familiarization \u2013** Understand different types of wood-burning freestanding stoves and their common features.\n\n**Freestanding Stove Inspection \u2013** Utilize the official NCSG checklist to thoroughly inspect wood-burning freestanding stoves.\n\n**Real-World Simulation \u2013** Complete the inspection by correctly identifying issues with maximum safety awareness and forensic skills.\n\nData reports for review are saved and stored for engagement metrics and simulation performance analysis.\n\nAny off-platform monetization of content accessible in this app conforms to the Oculus Bulk IAP or Subscription Licenses app policy outlined here: https://developer.oculus.com/policy/app-policies", "short_description": "The Hololab National Chimney Sweep Guild Wood Burning Freestanding Stoves VR application provides users with essential skills to inspect and maintain wood-burning freestanding stoves in compliance with NCSG standards. This course features interactive slide content, desktop-based activities, realistic simulations, and detailed testing."}]}, "developer_name": null, "developer_privacy_policy_url": "https://ftfvr.com/privacy-app/", "developer_terms_of_service_url": null, "publisher_name": "From the Future", "support_website_url": null, "website_ur